notes: Shower enclosure ~3.2m perimeter Ã 1.8m + bath splash 2mÂ²
embedding_text: WATERPROOF_WALL_AREA: Estimated waterproofing wall area. Shower enclosure perimeter ~3.2m Ã 1.8m height plus bath splash areas ~2mÂ² per bathroom.

notes: Bathroom, laundry, garage, etc.
embedding_text: NCC Part 10.3: Non-habitable rooms require minimum 2100mm ceiling height. This includes bathrooms, laundries, garages, and storage areas.

notes: 9 bedroom standard residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_9BR_STANDARD: 9 bedroom standard residential dwelling. GFA 460mÂ², 2 storey, 5 bathrooms. 2 garage. brick_veneer construction.

notes: +25% for C1 cyclonic region
embedding_text: AS 1684/AS 4055: Wind factor 1.25 for C1 cyclonic region. 25% increase for cyclone-rated construction. Northern Queensland, WA coast.

notes: 15% waste - roll width constraints, seam allowance
embedding_text: WASTE_CARPET: Carpet and vinyl waste factor 1.15 (15%). Higher waste due to roll width constraints, seam placement, and pattern matching requirements.

notes: Defaults to STOREYS (all storeys have bedrooms). Override if bedrooms only on one level.
embedding_text: BEDROOM_STOREY_COUNT: Number of storeys containing bedrooms. Defaults to total storeys. Override if bedrooms are only on specific levels.

notes: 8 bedroom premium residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_8BR_PREMIUM: 8 bedroom premium residential dwelling. GFA 540mÂ², 2 storey, 5 bathrooms. 4 garage. double_brick construction.

notes: Open plan layout - fewer internal walls
embedding_text: DENSITY_FACTOR_OPEN: Partition density factor 0.8 for open plan layouts. Reduces internal wall quantities for modern open living designs.

notes: +10% for N2 wind region
embedding_text: AS 1684/AS 4055: Wind factor 1.10 for N2 region. 10% increase in framing capacity. Most common residential classification.

notes: Shape complexity multiplier for perimeter (1.0 = perfect square, 1.2 = typical residential)
embedding_text: SHAPE_FACTOR: Shape complexity multiplier for building perimeter. Value 1.0 represents a perfect square, 1.2 is typical for residential with setbacks and articulation.

notes: Extra-over rate for excavation in unstable or running ground. Apply 1.50x multiplier. Includes additional shoring and stabilisation measures.
embedding_text: NRM2 extra-over unstable ground excavation 1.50x multiplier running sand loose fill collapsing trench shoring stabilisation

notes: BathÃ4 (WC, basin, shower, BTW) + KitchenÃ2 + LaundryÃ3
embedding_text: PLUMBING_FIXTURES: Estimated plumbing fixture count. Bathrooms Ã4 (WC, basin, shower, bath tap ware), kitchen Ã2 (sink, dishwasher), laundry Ã3 (tub, washer, dryer).

notes: 8 bedroom standard residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_8BR_STANDARD: 8 bedroom standard residential dwelling. GFA 400mÂ², 2 storey, 4 bathrooms. 2 garage. brick_veneer construction.

notes: Minimum exhaust flow rate for bathrooms
embedding_text: NCC Part 10.8.2: Bathroom exhaust fans must provide minimum 25 litres per second airflow. Required where no openable window.

notes: General stairs maximum rise
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.2: Maximum stair riser height is 190mm for general stairs in Class 1 and 2 buildings per Table 11.2.2a.

notes: Timber framing area adjusted for wind class. Structural design governs final.
embedding_text: FRAME_AREA: Estimated timber framing area. GFA Ã 2.4 Ã wind factor. The 2.4 factor accounts for walls + ceiling frame. Wind factor adjusts for bracing requirements.

notes: 15% glazing ratio - NOT an NCC requirement, just estimating default
embedding_text: WINDOW_AREA_DEFAULT: Default window area is 15% of external wall area. This is an estimating heuristic, NOT an NCC requirement. Actual glazing varies by design.

notes: 5% waste - spillage, over-excavation, pump residue
embedding_text: WASTE_CONCRETE: Concrete waste factor 1.05 (5%). Accounts for spillage during pour, over-excavation of footings, pump line residue, and minor overruns.

notes: 5 bedroom premium residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_5BR_PREMIUM: 5 bedroom premium residential dwelling. GFA 297mÂ², 2 storey, 4 bathrooms. 3 garage. double_brick construction. 8.4m balustrade.

notes: General stairs maximum going
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.2: Maximum stair going (tread depth) is 355mm for general stairs per Table 11.2.2a.

notes: Approx 3m run Ã 1.5m width per flight
embedding_text: STAIR_AREA: Estimated stair area is (storeys - 1) Ã 4.5 square metres. Assumes approximately 3m run Ã 1.5m width per flight including landing.

notes: 4 bedroom standard residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_4BR_STANDARD: 4 bedroom standard residential dwelling. GFA 180mÂ², 1 storey, 2 bathrooms. 1 garage. brick_veneer construction.

notes: Compartmentalised layout - many rooms
embedding_text: DENSITY_FACTOR_COMPARTMENT: Partition density factor 1.4 for compartmentalised layouts. Many separate rooms, traditional designs, home offices.

notes: Areas with ceiling below 1500mm excluded from floor area calculation
embedding_text: NCC Part 10.3: Areas where ceiling height is less than 1500mm are excluded from floor area calculations for sloping ceiling compliance.

notes: 10 bedroom standard residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_10BR_STANDARD: 10 bedroom standard residential dwelling. GFA 520mÂ², 2 storey, 5 bathrooms. 2 garage. brick_veneer construction.

notes: 6 bedroom premium residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_6BR_PREMIUM: 6 bedroom premium residential dwelling. GFA 378mÂ², 2 storey, 4 bathrooms. 3 garage. double_brick construction.

notes: 7 bedroom standard residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_7BR_STANDARD: 7 bedroom standard residential dwelling. GFA 340mÂ², 2 storey, 4 bathrooms. 2 garage. brick_veneer construction.

notes: Maximum risers before a landing is required
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.2: Maximum 18 risers per flight before a landing is required for Class 1 and 2 buildings.

notes: 5 bedroom standard residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_5BR_STANDARD: 5 bedroom standard residential dwelling. GFA 220mÂ², 2 storey, 3 bathrooms. 2 garage. brick_veneer construction. 8.4m balustrade.

notes: Natural ventilation: openable area >= 5% of floor area
embedding_text: NCC Part 10.6: Natural ventilation requires openable area of at least 5% of floor area for habitable rooms. Can use mechanical ventilation as alternative.

notes: 3 bedroom premium residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_3BR_PREMIUM: 3 bedroom premium residential dwelling. GFA 175mÂ², 1 storey, 3 bathrooms. 2 garage. double_brick construction.

notes: Both sides of internal partitions
embedding_text: PLASTERBOARD_AREA: Total plasterboard area for internal partitions. Equals single-sided partition area Ã 2 for both faces of walls.

notes: 10% waste - sheet layout offcuts, corner damage
embedding_text: WASTE_PLASTERBOARD: Plasterboard waste factor 1.10 (10%). Accounts for sheet layout offcuts, corner and edge damage during installation.

notes: Voids less than 5.00mÂ² are not deducted from formwork quantities. Only large openings such as stairwells and lift shafts are deducted.
embedding_text: NRM2 formwork void deduction threshold 5.00 square metres large openings stairwells lift shafts deducted concrete shuttering

notes: Building footprint - CRITICAL: use this for perimeter/roof, NOT GFA_TOTAL
embedding_text: FOOTPRINT_AREA: Building footprint area equals GFA divided by number of storeys. CRITICAL for multi-storey buildings - use footprint for perimeter and roof calculations, not total GFA.

notes: 125mm sphere test - no opening to permit passage
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.3: Maximum opening in balustrades is 125mm - the sphere test. No opening should permit passage of a 125mm sphere to prevent child entrapment.

notes: Number of bedrooms - used for smoke alarm, electrical calculations
embedding_text: BEDROOM_COUNT: Number of bedrooms in the dwelling. Used for smoke alarm requirements, electrical calculations, and hot water system sizing.

notes: Total ceiling area = total floor area
embedding_text: CEILING_AREA: Total ceiling plasterboard area equals footprint Ã storeys. Does not include bulkheads or dropped ceilings.

notes: Minimum ceiling height for habitable rooms (excluding kitchen)
embedding_text: NCC Part 10.3: Minimum ceiling height for habitable rooms in Class 1 and 2 buildings is 2400mm. This is a mandatory Deemed-to-Satisfy requirement. Excludes kitchens which are classified as non-habitable.

notes: Shallow excavation up to 250mm depth. Typically surface stripping, topsoil removal, or minor levelling works.
embedding_text: NRM2 excavation depth classification shallow 0.25m 250mm surface stripping topsoil removal levelling

notes: Front + rear/garage entry
embedding_text: EXTERNAL_DOOR_COUNT: Default 2 external doors - front entry door and rear/side/garage entry. Excludes sliding doors.

notes: General barrier height where drop exceeds 1m
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.3: Minimum balustrade height is 1000mm where fall height exceeds 1 metre. This applies to balconies, decks, stairs, and landings.

notes: Deep excavation between 1.00m and 2.00m depth. May require edge protection and battering. Shoring considerations.

notes: 10% waste - cut-ins, breakage, pattern matching
embedding_text: WASTE_TILES: Floor and wall tile waste factor 1.10 (10%). Accounts for cut-ins around fixtures, breakage during cutting, pattern matching at edges.

notes: Internal stair barrier where drop is less than 1m
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.3: Internal stair barriers can be 865mm minimum where drop is less than 1 metre.

notes: Headroom above stair nosing line
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.2: Minimum headroom above stair nosing line is 2000mm. Measured perpendicular from nosing line to any obstruction above.

notes: Facade envelope area (gross, before opening deductions)
embedding_text: EXTERNAL_WALL_AREA_GROSS: Total facade envelope area before deducting windows and doors. Calculated as perimeter Ã storeys Ã ceiling height. Used for cladding, insulation, and sarking.

notes: Bath walls (no shower) waterproofed to 150mm above vessel lip
embedding_text: NCC Part 10.2 / AS 3740: Bath walls without shower require waterproofing to 150mm above the bath vessel lip.

notes: 2R+G comfort formula maximum
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.2: Stair comfort formula 2R+G must not exceed 700mm. This ensures comfortable stepping rhythm.

notes: Standard residential layout
embedding_text: DENSITY_FACTOR_TYPICAL: Partition density factor 1.1 for standard residential layouts. Represents typical room configurations with separate bedrooms, living, dining.

notes: 6 bedroom standard residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_6BR_STANDARD: 6 bedroom standard residential dwelling. GFA 280mÂ², 2 storey, 3 bathrooms. 2 garage. brick_veneer construction.

notes: Minimum exhaust flow rate for kitchens (must be ducted externally)
embedding_text: NCC Part 10.8.2: Kitchen rangehood exhaust must provide minimum 40 litres per second and be ducted externally. Required where no openable window.

embedding_text: NCC Part 9.5 Compliant: Minimum smoke alarms equals storeys with bedrooms plus bedroom hallways. Interconnected, mains-powered with battery backup required.

notes: Minimum distance from cornice/wall junction
embedding_text: NCC Part 9.5: Smoke alarms must be at least 300mm from cornice or wall junction. Prevents dead air pockets affecting detection.

embedding_text: SLAB_AREA: Ground floor slab area equals building footprint. Does not include garage if separate or suspended floors above.

notes: Facade envelope area net of openings

notes: Habitable room ceiling height - bounded by NCC 2.4m minimum
embedding_text: CEILING_HEIGHT_HAB: Default ceiling height for habitable rooms is 2.7 metres. This is bounded by NCC minimum of 2.4m. Used for wall area and internal volume calculations.

expression: CASE WHEN depth <= 0.50 THEN shallow WHEN depth <= 1.00 THEN medium WHEN depth <= 1.50 THEN deep ELSE very_deep END

embedding_text: NRM2 drainage trench depth classification shallow medium deep very deep 0.5m 1.0m 1.5m service trenches pipes sewers

notes: 100mm slab with 5% concrete waste
embedding_text: SLAB_VOLUME: Concrete volume for ground slab. Footprint Ã 100mm thickness Ã 1.05 waste factor. Standard residential slab on ground.

notes: Base multiplier for N1 wind region
embedding_text: AS 1684/AS 4055: Wind factor 1.00 for N1 region. Base reference for framing and fixing requirements. Low wind exposure.

notes: Extra-over rate for excavation in waterlogged ground. Apply 1.35x multiplier. Includes pumping, dewatering, and working in wet conditions.

notes: 1 bedroom premium residential template

notes: 5% waste - overlap allowance, end waste
embedding_text: WASTE_ROOF_METAL: Metal roofing waste factor 1.05 (5%). Lower waste due to cut-to-length ordering. Accounts for overlaps and minor end waste.

notes: Sydney/Brisbane default assumption
embedding_text: WIND_CLASS_DEFAULT: Default wind classification N2 for Sydney, Brisbane, Melbourne metro areas. Non-cyclonic region with moderate wind exposure.

notes: General stairs minimum going (tread depth)
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.2: Minimum stair going (tread depth) is 240mm for general stairs per Table 11.2.2a.

notes: Maximum gap from floor edge to barrier face (NCC 2022 update)
embedding_text: NCC 2022 Update: Maximum gap between floor edge and barrier face is 40mm. This prevents small children from sliding under balustrades.

notes: 4 bedroom premium residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_4BR_PREMIUM: 4 bedroom premium residential dwelling. GFA 243mÂ², 1 storey, 3 bathrooms. 2 garage. double_brick construction.

embedding_text: ROOF_FACTOR: Roof area multiplier accounting for pitch and eaves. Value 1.15 represents typical pitched roof. Flat roof would be 1.0, steep pitch up to 1.3.

notes: 1 bedroom standard residential template

notes: Minimum width between handrails
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.2: Minimum stair width between handrails is 600mm for Class 1 and 2 buildings.

notes: Roof area including pitch factor and eaves. Based on FOOTPRINT not GFA.

notes: Extra-over rate for excavation in rock. Apply 2.5x multiplier to base excavation rate. Includes rock breaking, removal, and disposal.

notes: Habitable attic with sloping ceiling (over 2/3 of area)

notes: 1 per dwelling (size based on bedrooms)

notes: External perimeter from footprint (not GFA). Shape factor 1.2 accounts for non-square layouts.

notes: At least 2/3 of floor area must meet minimum height for sloping ceilings
embedding_text: NCC Part 10.3: For sloping ceilings, at least two-thirds (66.7%) of the floor area must meet the minimum ceiling height requirement.

notes: Voids less than 0.50mÂ² are not deducted from masonry quantities. This applies to small windows, vents, and service openings.

notes: 7% waste - breakage, half-bricks, weathering
embedding_text: WASTE_MASONRY: Brickwork and blockwork waste factor 1.07 (7%). Accounts for breakage during delivery/handling, cutting half-bricks, weathering on site.

notes: 2 bedroom standard residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_2BR_STANDARD: 2 bedroom standard residential dwelling. GFA 90mÂ², 1 storey, 1 bathroom. 1 garage. brick_veneer construction.

notes: Strip footing excavation (no waste - removed from site)
embedding_text: EXCAVATION_VOLUME: Excavation volume for strip footings. No waste factor - material removed from site. Add bulking factor for disposal calculation.

notes: +20% for N3 wind region
embedding_text: AS 1684/AS 4055: Wind factor 1.20 for N3 region. 20% increase in framing requirements. Elevated or exposed sites.

notes: Number of storeys - user input or inferred
embedding_text: STOREYS: Number of storeys or levels in the building. User input or inferred from project description. Used to calculate footprint area and vertical elements.

notes: BedsÃ4 + LivingÃ6 + KitchenÃ8 + BathÃ2 + GarageÃ2. NO NCC minimum.
embedding_text: POWER_POINTS: Estimated power point count. Bedrooms Ã4, living areas Ã6, kitchen Ã8, bathrooms Ã2, garage Ã2. No NCC minimum - design based on practical use.

notes: Minimum exhaust flow rate for laundries
embedding_text: NCC Part 10.8.2: Laundry exhaust must provide minimum 40 litres per second. Required where no openable window.

notes: Corridors/hallways associated with bedrooms. Min 1, then 1 per 4 bedrooms.

notes: 7 bedroom premium residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_7BR_PREMIUM: 7 bedroom premium residential dwelling. GFA 459mÂ², 2 storey, 5 bathrooms. 3 garage. double_brick construction.

notes: Typical 1 sliding door to outdoor area
embedding_text: SLIDING_DOOR_COUNT: Default 1 sliding door to outdoor entertainment area. Bifold or stacker doors count separately based on design.

notes: 2R+G comfort formula minimum (NOT RÃG product)
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.2: Stair comfort formula 2R+G must be at least 550mm. This is 2 times the rise plus the going. Common misunderstanding - this is NOT rise Ã going.

notes: General stairs minimum rise
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.2: Minimum stair riser height is 115mm for general stairs in Class 1 and 2 buildings per Table 11.2.2a.

notes: Number of bathrooms - used for plumbing, waterproofing calculations
embedding_text: BATHROOM_COUNT: Number of bathrooms including ensuites. Used for plumbing fixtures, waterproofing area, and exhaust fan calculations.

notes: Practical default for furniture/move-in (not NCC requirement)
embedding_text: STAIR_WIDTH_DEFAULT: Recommended stair width of 900mm for practical use and furniture moving. This exceeds NCC minimum of 600mm but is common residential practice.

notes: 2 bedroom premium residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_2BR_PREMIUM: 2 bedroom premium residential dwelling. GFA 121mÂ², 1 storey, 2 bathrooms. 2 garage. double_brick construction.

notes: If no corridor, alarm must be within 1500mm of bedroom entrance
embedding_text: NCC Part 9.5: Where no corridor exists, smoke alarm must be within 1500mm of bedroom entrance. Ensures early warning for sleeping occupants.

notes: Gross Floor Area - user input or inferred from description
embedding_text: GFA_TOTAL: Gross Floor Area in square metres. User input or inferred from project description. This is the total floor area of the building including all storeys.

notes: 10 bedroom premium residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_10BR_PREMIUM: 10 bedroom premium residential dwelling. GFA 702mÂ², 2 storey, 6 bathrooms. 4 garage. double_brick construction.

notes: Kitchen classified as non-habitable for ceiling height purposes
embedding_text: NCC Part 10.3: Kitchen minimum ceiling height is 2100mm. Kitchens are classified as non-habitable rooms for ceiling height purposes in the NCC.

notes: 10% waste - offcuts, knots, site damage
embedding_text: WASTE_TIMBER: Timber framing waste factor 1.10 (10%). Accounts for cutting offcuts, rejection of knotty/damaged pieces, site handling damage.

notes: Single-sided partition area. Normalized for ceiling height.
embedding_text: INTERNAL_PARTITION_1SIDE: Single-sided internal partition wall area. Calculated from floor area Ã density factor, normalized for ceiling height. Represents one face of internal walls.

notes: Perimeter + 15% for internal bearings
embedding_text: FOOTING_LENGTH: Total strip footing length. External perimeter plus 15% for internal loadbearing walls. Used for excavation and concrete quantities.

notes: Medium excavation between 250mm and 1.00m depth. Standard foundation trenches and service runs.

notes: Approx 2 external doors at 2040x820mm each = 3.35mÂ²
embedding_text: DOOR_AREA_EXTERNAL: Default external door area assuming 2 doors at standard size 2040mm Ã 820mm = approximately 3.35 square metres total.

notes: 8% waste - ridge/hip cuts, breakage
embedding_text: WASTE_ROOF_TILES: Roof tile waste factor 1.08 (8%). Accounts for ridge and hip cutting, breakage during installation, and starter course.

notes: Shower walls waterproofed to minimum 1800mm above floor substrate
embedding_text: NCC Part 10.2 / AS 3740: Shower walls must be waterproofed to minimum 1800mm above floor substrate level. Includes all shower enclosure walls.

notes: Window protection required if fall height >= 2000mm
embedding_text: NCC Part 11.3: Window fall protection measures required where external fall height is 2000mm or greater.

notes: 9 bedroom premium residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_9BR_PREMIUM: 9 bedroom premium residential dwelling. GFA 621mÂ², 2 storey, 6 bathrooms. 4 garage. double_brick construction.

notes: Approx: bathrooms 6mÂ², ensuites 4mÂ², laundry 6mÂ²
embedding_text: WATERPROOF_FLOOR_AREA: Estimated waterproofing floor area. Bathrooms average 6mÂ², ensuites 4mÂ², laundry 6mÂ². Entire wet area floor must be waterproofed.

notes: 3 bedroom standard residential template
embedding_text: ARCHETYPE_3BR_STANDARD: 3 bedroom standard residential dwelling. GFA 130mÂ², 1 storey, 2 bathrooms. 1 garage. brick_veneer construction.

notes: Approx 1 light per 10mÂ². NO NCC minimum.
embedding_text: LIGHT_POINTS: Estimated light point count. Approximately 1 light per 10 square metres of floor area. Includes downlights, pendants, wall lights.
